The Active filter is selected, so the app renders only the active todo — the
completed one is filtered out and produces no `<li>`, hence no line. The filter
list projects `All (Active) Completed`. The counter and the Clear-completed
segment reflect the whole model (a completed todo still exists), not the shown
list.
Pins: Active selected → `(Active)`; filtered-out todo produces no line; counter
and Clear-completed follow the model, not the view.

-- dom.html --
<section class="todoapp">
	<header class="header">
		<h1>todos</h1>
		<input class="new-todo" placeholder="What needs to be done?">
	</header>
	<section class="main">
		<input id="toggle-all" class="toggle-all" type="checkbox">
		<label for="toggle-all">Mark all as complete</label>
		<ul class="todo-list">
			<li data-id="t1">
				<div class="view">
					<input class="toggle" type="checkbox">
					<label>buy milk</label>
					<button class="destroy"></button>
				</div>
				<input class="edit" value="buy milk">
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
	<footer class="footer">
		<span class="todo-count"><strong>1</strong> item left</span>
		<ul class="filters">
			<li><a href="/">All</a></li>
			<li><a class="selected" href="/active">Active</a></li>
			<li><a href="/completed">Completed</a></li>
		</ul>
		<button class="clear-completed">Clear completed</button>
	</footer>
</section>

-- projection.txt --
v > ""
#t1 [ ] buy milk
-- **1** item left | All (Active) Completed | [Clear completed]
